WorkItem.ClosedComment:
This is very much intentional.

For example, consider Array#forEach. Its callback provides you three parameters, but the great majority of code using it only uses (and declares) the first parameter. It would be burdensome and pointless to force you to declare more parameters than you need.

This is also important for functions that take some variable number of arguments and operate directly on the arguments array.

Note that it's basically impossible to come up with a plausible scenario where you would accidently write too few parameters in a function implementation.
